				<wikidot:authorName>mickeyten</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4444390</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>To my taste this is actually superior to 3999, with more internal consistency, staying firmly in-universe (and, tbh, meta articles like 3999 really grate on me - again, just personal taste), and the format screw here is a breath of fresh air. And as Cyantreuse said above, this is an absolutely immersive dive into what it could be like to <em>really</em> work for the Foundation.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
